article.headline: SE Louisiana 95, Dillard 53
article.story: EDS: SE Louisiana 95, Dillard 53. jm:hout HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Warrell Span and Kevyn Green scored 20 points each as Southeastern Louisiana beat Dillard Community College 95-53 Friday night. The Lions (6-3) hit 61 percent of their shots from the floor and held the Blue Devils (4-3) to 29 percent. They led 44-27 at halftime. Tavaris Nance had 17 points for Southeastern, freshman Daryl Arnold had 15 in his first start, and Patrick Sullivan and Dekyron Nicks had 10 points each. David Manning had 16 points and 12 rebounds for Dillard. Autrail Manning and Marlon Washington had 11 points each and Darnell Williams 10.
